1️⃣ Navigation & Entry

A “Create an Agent” button is visible on the Marketplace homepage.

Clicking the button opens a dedicated “Create an Agent” page.

Page is accessible only to authenticated users.

Page follows Marketplace UI design standards.

2️⃣ Overview Section

The page must include:

A short explanation of what an agent is in this ecosystem.

A brief explanation of why ADK is required.

A high-level diagram or visual explaining:

Build → Register → Publish → Use

3️⃣ Step-by-Step Creation Instructions

The page must clearly display the standardized workflow:

Step 1 – Build the Agent

Description of using Lingo Agent ADK

Clear link to the Lingo Agent ADK repository

Link opens in a new tab

Instructions mention:

Boilerplate generation

Metadata definition

Key generation (JWKS)

Logging requirements

Step 2 – Prepare Agent Metadata

List required metadata fields:

Agent Name

Description

Owner

Business Unit

Version

Capabilities

JWKS URL

Manifest URL

Clearly state metadata must align with Registry schema.

Link to metadata specification documentation.

Step 3 – Agent Registration (2-Step Process)

The page must explicitly explain:

Step 3A – Registry Submission

Agent submits metadata to Registry.

Registry generates Agent ID.

Agent receives confirmation of registration.

Step 3B – Marketplace Publication

After Registry registration, agent must be published to Marketplace.

Publication may require review/approval.

Agent appears as:

Public (synthetic-safe)

Private (restricted)

The 2-step process must be clearly labeled visually.

Step 4 – Post-Registration Actions

The page must list next steps:

Enable Playground (if eligible)

Configure access approval workflow

Set capability visibility

Define version policy

Monitor usage

4️⃣ Governance Notice

Page must clearly state:

All agents must use ADK standards.

All agents must comply with security and logging requirements.

Agents handling PHI require additional approval.

Marketplace listing does not equal automatic client access.

5️⃣ Links & Documentation

The page must include:

ADK Repository Link

Metadata Schema Documentation Link

Registration API Documentation Link

Security Requirements Documentation Link

Contact/Support Channel

All links must be validated and open in new tabs.

6️⃣ Error Handling & States

If documentation links are unavailable, display fallback error message.

If user lacks permission to view page, display access denied message.

If feature is under maintenance, display banner notification.

7️⃣ Non-Functional Requirements

Page loads within acceptable UI performance threshold.

Page is mobile-responsive.

Page follows accessibility guidelines (WCAG compliant).

Page supports versioned documentation updates.

Page content is maintainable via content configuration (not hardcoded if possible).
